      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "> @willcl-ark also noted a while back that he saw high CPU usage with the utxocache events during IBD. So might be interesting to check this.\n\nWould only note here that this was done on a Hetzner CX22, with 2 vCPUs, 4 GB of RAM, and 40 GB of disk space. This is already pretty-constrained for a pruning full node doing IBD, but I was also obviously running the IPC collector on the same machine. ",
